    "finalTextLength": 1786,
    "finalText": "Current coverage is degraded — you’re not seeing a fully up-to-date picture. Here’s exactly where things stand:\n\n**1. Teams and Outlook sync is suffering.**\n- Multiple key mailboxes (njepson, mparsons, mharrison, jdawson, ctragesser) and at least one Teams DM export (acannon) are flagged as critical. This means recent emails or Teams chats from these sources are likely missing or delayed. If any major discussion is happening on their channels, assume it’s not captured in the most recent readout.\n\n**2. Knowledge packets are behind.**\n- Over 11,500 source items are uncompiled, and 1,065 items are pending embedding. That means readouts and \"AI summaries\" for meetings, projects, or cross-project intelligence may be missing recent updates, especially anything from the last few days or newly uploaded content.\n\n**3. Meeting coverage is only as good as source ingestion.**\n- If meetings were held recently and included in an out-of-sync mailbox or a not-yet-embedded transcript, they won’t appear in “AI” briefings until the pipeline catches up.\n\n**Bottom line**\n- Anything you pull today may be missing the latest decisions or problems aired in those key channels — especially if they involve staff on the flagged Outlook or Teams endpoints.\n- For absolutely current status, double-check live email and Teams if you suspect a gap, or ask me to pull raw/uncompiled sources by name/date if you want to cover the blind spot.\n\n**Recommendation**\n- Don’t use AI readouts as the single source of truth for time-sensitive issues until sync health is restored. If you need eyes on something critical, call out exactly which channel or meeting to cross-check.\n\nLet me know if you want a focused deep dive on a specific project or date range — I’ll look for raw evidence, not just summaries.",
